a0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:7pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">23-05-13. Supporting statement.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The above covered a period of over seven months and contains 51 A4 documents involving many </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">departments incurring costs to the public purse and costs to myself.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The result of this complaints procedure was that my complaint was outside the Ombudsman’s adjudication.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I would like to offer this evidence to the select committee review on the grounds </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">that a large amount of money, both mine and the public’s, could have been saved if I had been given the correct advice on 17th October 2012.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">After experiencing the above, and the waste of time, energy and public money, I have come to the conclusion that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">if a member of the general public has a complaint against their local authority then there should be a mechanism in place to determine if the local government Ombudsman can investigate that complaint. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">By following the advice of the local authority I prev</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ented the Local Government Ombudsman being able to investigate my case. In turn the Ombudsman advised me to follow a procedure that was outside his jurisdiction. He did not advise me of this loss of right or tell me about Fact Sheet G2 (which I finally rec</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">eived 30</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:super">th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> April 2013, 6 months after I first approached the Ombudsman) before I started my complaints procedure.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">If the select committee require any supporting evidence to the above statement I will be more than happy to supply it.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">If the select committe</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e would like me to give oral evidence I will also be more than happy to accommodate.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Listed below is all the documented evidence in date order.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.32pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">14th of October 2011 we informed the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Forest</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Dean</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> planning that our neighbour had excavated the grass verge running down one side of the Lane and built a 2m high wall, without legal authority, which encroaches onto the highway.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Two thirds of the wall being on the publicly maintained highway and one thir</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">d on the forestry track. This reduced the width of the Lane to 2½ m.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.32pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">9th of December 2011. We received a letter informing us that a cessation of works had been issued and that we would be kept informed.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.32pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">During January and February 2012 we made several phon</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e calls and were informed by the planning officer that the encroachment would be dealt with under a retrospective planning application which was submitted on 30th March 2012.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.32pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">27th of June 2012 (public record) Gloucestershire Highways no observations with n</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">o mention of the encroachment.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.32pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">4th of July 2012 e-mail from Gloucestershire fire and rescue stating they were unable to pass the newly constructed boundary wall and that their hoses would fall short. Encroachment impeded all emergency vehicles.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.32pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">6th of July</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> 2012. I took the day off work and had a meeting with the planning officer at the Council offices. He informed me that he was waiting for highways to get back to him about the encroachment. At 15:29 pm of the same day I phoned Gloucestershire highways who </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">claimed to have no request from the planning officer.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">After explaining our difficulties</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> to them </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I was advised that the encroachment on to the publicly maintained h</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ighway was the H</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ighways responsibility but the encroachment on to the forestry track</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> was priv</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ate land.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">P</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">art </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">of the Highway Act</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> deals with this type of the encroachment </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">so </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I should look it up.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.32pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">8th July 2012. I sent Gloucestershire Highways Form 1 under the Highways Act 1980 requiring a local highway authority to secure the removal of an obstruction</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. This was acknowledged on 16 July 2012. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.32pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">20th of July 2012. A meeting was held in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Marians Lane</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> with Highways and Planning and I was told that this would be handed over to their legal Department.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.32pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Gloucestershire Highways failed to comply with the procedure</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s set out in the act - no receipt of Form 2; no receipt of Form 3; no returning of phone calls; no correspondence. This failure by the Highway Authority to comply with the requirements of this procedure under Highways Act 1980 left me with no choice but to</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> issue Form 4 giving notice of my attention to apply to the Magistrates Court. This I did on the 24</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:super">th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> September 2012.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Gloucestershire highways are claiming ignorance of the law and this failure to comply with the highways act is an oversight.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.32pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">28th of September 2012. A meeting was held in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Marians Lane</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> with Highways and the Forestry Commission. Unfortunately this meeting came to an abrupt end when the landowner turned up giving verbal abuse and threatening behaviour. The police were called and th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e incident is recorded. The landowner was given a warning.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.32pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">2nd of October 2012. Still having not received any correspondence or any of my phone calls returned it left me with no alternative but to apply to the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Magistrates Court</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> for an order to require our </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">local authority to take action for the removal of this unlawful obstruction.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.32pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">17th October 2012. I received a letter dated 15th October 2012 which was the result of a meeting on 12th October 2012 between Gloucestershire Highways and their legal Department. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Claiming this was the wrong procedure, on a factually wrong statement, which excluded section 222 of the local government </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">A</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ct 1972. Protection of inhabitants and contravened article 1 of protocol 1 protection of property</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> under the human rights </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">A</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ct.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">It ha</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s now been over two years and this unlawful, wilful, obstruction of our Lane still remains. It seems I can do nothing about this and it has cost me £7500 to find this out because of incorrect advice from Government departments. Is this fair? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Exclusive su</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">mmary</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Report a crime - lose your home</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The Local Authority can give you information that will exclude the Local Government Ombudsman’s right to investigate your complaint and then the Ombudsman can do the same thing. This has resulted in my case, in me be</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ing about to lose my home.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:right"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">16th November 2013</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>